<plot>One Square Mile examines the Lake Como community in Fort Worth, Texas; a neighborhood born out of segregation a century ago, which now tries to cope with the effects of its heritage. This square mile of struggle and triumph can be seen as a microcosm of the larger issues of race and economics in America.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?412648</url></doc>
